import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_code_counts = data['zip_code'].value_counts()
    zip_codes = zip_code_counts.index
    frequencies = zip_code_counts.values

    plt.bar(zip_codes, frequencies)
    plt.xlabel('Zip Codes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    city_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(state_counts, labels=state_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(state_counts.index, loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    county_counts = data['county'].value_counts()
    county_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('County')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Counties'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between latitude and longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
